evel 63 cm and Ecopit 8 - level 23 cm."],["10","Continued with site inspections; 2 done this week at M30B and Thermal desorption facility."],["11","Sent to National Environmental Agency the quarterly reporting of Oil and Gas exploration and production permit."],["12","Started the monitoring program with third parties"]]}],"subsections":[{"title":"HSSE","paragraphs":[],"tables":[]},{"title":"INCIDENTS","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["Incident Code","Date","Brief Description"],["ALB0526Mvi004","07-May-26","One of the north area operators while reversing his Toyota pickup truck at N26B, made contact with the pipeline support. The tailgate was damaged and the rear signal indicator on the passenger side was broken."],["ALB0526NM002","09-May-26","While V.Bistika trailer was unloading a rod box near well 5451 - N27B, at approximately 70-80 cm from the ground the rod plastic bundles slipped off and the rod box landed on ground on one side. No injuries or damage reported."]]}]},{"title":"STATUS","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"],["1","Continue with safety orientation (15( and H2S training (10) employees."],["2","Safety meeting were held with crews working at Kallmi bridge."],["3","Received the final decision of Regional Environmental Agency inspection of Ecopit 4 and its permit."],["4","Received the final decision of REA inspection at Ecopit 6."],["5","Received the notification on REA inspection of 3.2.B license"]]}]},{"title":"ACTIONS","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"],["1","Continue cooperating with tech support team for hot work permits 22 in total."],["2","13 Site Work Inspections performed by HS Team."],["3","Safety team has been daily for safety support at the Kallmi bridge. Also safety supports done at L26A and O32A"],["4",""],["5","8 Gas readings requested by the operations team performed last week."],["6","Four tank trucks inspected."],["7","11 fire suppression systems inspected by the fire department. One