t PDU of pad P32A repeated.","J165 at N28A is ready for operation. Waiting confirmation from RET to start 5142","Active injectors are 33. Average injection 69m3/day/injector. While 4 of the reactivates one remains SI to monitor pattern performance","Normal operation to PSU300 (run with 79%). PSU600 is running with 37%.","Av. daily polymer FP36330S consumption of the week was 3.2 bags. Stocks in store are 200 bags (11 May)","The main changes in injector’s performance during the last week have been:","Drop of injection rate to 5015/D4 by 10m3/d as well to 5478/D3U by 6m3/d (WHP)","WHP of 5891/D3U increased to 70psi. Restarted J165 pump.","The injection rate of 6108/M was stabilized"],"tables":[{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]}]},{"title":"6.2.2 OTHERS","paragraphs":["Under strict monitor the 4 self-producing WSW in G1 and G2 zone due to high reservoir energy. Max casing pressure at WSW 963/G1 remains at 150psi.","10 WSW are in production. WSW 1467 start & stop depending steam project demand.","It was received letter from AMBU regarding the fresh water consumption in Q1-2026. The request for payment will be submitted in OA system.","Hot water with Surfactant and Viscosity Reducer, Huff & Puff.","6002/M – to recover 764m3; FDT 245m; W/C 90%","5577/G4: to recover 1066m3; FDT 150m; Net 1.9m3/d","5284/G4: to recover 1733m3; FDT 1176m","5836/D3L: to recover 31.6m3; FDT 228m; Net 3.4m3/d","5614/G6: to recover 13819m3; FDT 708m"],"tables":[{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]}]},{"title":"6.2.3 NEW CONVERSION 2026","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["Wells for Conversion","Injection well","PAD","Mixing Area","First Injection Date","Comments"]]}]},{"title":"WEEKLY WELL SERVICES","paragraphs":[],"tables":[]},{"title":"SUMMARY","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["Double rig and Single Rigs SS18/SS19","6 jobs completed by Double rig and Single Rigs SS18/SS19"],["Flush by Rig SS17","8 jobs completed by Flush by rig SS17"],["Rig less Jobs","2 wells/jobs - completed by Rig les