  ('7736a974-ef0c-502f-8d8b-d24cc2413bd9'::uuid, 'reservoir', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-05-31 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"25-31 May 2026","starts_on":"2026-05-25","ends_on":"2026-05-31","department_id":"reservoir","paragraphs":["Completed all pattern review of N28B pads and decided to restart polymer injection of 5392, 5393，5505，5394 and 5507.","Updated all long SI polymer producer list to screen reactivation candidates.","Updated 2508-M reactivation evaluation.","Discussed with Production, EOR and Workover departments and decided to reactivate 5759, 5649 and implement polymer conversion of 5400.","Actual Production Vs. 2026 Budget as of May 31th, 2026","Five polymer producers have weekly production incremental higher than 2m3/d.","Production recover after workover –5367, 951,5602,5877,5899.","One polymer producer has weekly production loss equal/higher than 2 m3/d.","Less run time due to workover: 5996.","The average injection volume in the last week was 2342m3/d from 2243m3/d or 99m3/d more than the previous week. The main issues have been:","Instrument problem at PSU300 on May 25th. Air system leakage","Electrical issue of J165 VFD at O32B on 25 May. Replaced with the VFD of J165 of O29A. The VFD of O32B is at the electrical shop, Pad H to be fixed.","Electrical issue in mission pump at N31B. It was repeated continuously. Replaced VFD of mission pump.","Mechanical issue on J165 pump at L31A. Was found leakage (crack) on fluid end. It was replaced with the fluid end of J165 moved from N28A","Active injectors are 40. Restarted 5 injectors. Average injection 58.5m3/day/injector. While 3 of the reactivates injectors remains SI to monitor pattern performance","PSU300 is running with 78%. PSU600 is running with 41% of capacity.","Av. daily polymer FP36330S consumption of the week was 3.3 bags. Restarted 5 injectors at N28B pad. Stocks in store are 135 bags (on 31 May)","The main changes in injector’s performance during the 