uid end. It was replaced with the fluid end of J165 moved from N28A","Active injectors are 40. Restarted 5 injectors. Average injection 58.5m3/day/injector. While 3 of the reactivates injectors remains SI to monitor pattern performance","PSU300 is running with 78%. PSU600 is running with 41% of capacity.","Av. daily polymer FP36330S consumption of the week was 3.3 bags. Restarted 5 injectors at N28B pad. Stocks in store are 135 bags (on 31 May)","The main changes in injector’s performance during the last week have been:","Drop of injection at 5802/M by 12% and 5645/M2 by 15%"],"tables":[{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]}]},{"title":"Injection rate and WHP at 5865/D3L continues stable","paragraphs":["Increased the injection rate of 6108/M by 25%. Uninterrupted injection effect"],"tables":[]},{"title":"6.2.2 OTHERS","paragraphs":["Under strict monitor the 4 self-producing WSW in G1 and G2 zone due to high reservoir energy. Max casing pressure at WSW 963/G1 remains at 150psi.","10 WSW are in production. Increased the volume of fresh water used for the dust control in the roads.","Preparations for the high temperatures of the season are ongoing.","Discussed and approved the conversion of 5400 into a polymer injector. Worked to prepare a temporary injection system for the test period (until the end of vacuum period).","Hot water with Surfactant and Viscosity Reducer, Huff & Puff.","6002/M – to recover 497.8m3; FDT 189m; Net 3.2m3/d","5577/G4: to recover 1024m3; FDT 271m; Net 1.9m3/d","5284/G4: to recover 1733m3; FDT 1176m","5614/G6: to recover 13819m3; FDT 708m"],"tables":[{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]}]},{"title":"6.2.3 NEW CONVERSION 2026","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["Wells for Conversion","Injection well","PAD","Mixing Area","First Injection Date","Comments"]]}]},{"title":"WEEKLY WELL SERVICES","paragraphs":[],"tables":[]},{"title":"SUMMARY","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["Double rig and Single Rigs SS18/SS19","8 jobs completed by Double rig and