ly report of Ecopit 5 and Ecopit 6 permits."],["12","Continued with environmental lease inspections."]]}],"subsections":[{"title":"HSSE","paragraphs":[],"tables":[]},{"title":"INCIDENTS","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["Incident Code","Date","Brief Description"],["ALB0226MTI001","03-Feb-26","An incident with injury has been reported by the well servicing Manager Gurim Premce at 1440 on 3rd February. The incident occurred at Superstar RSS019 rig around 11:00 AM but wasn''t reported on time. While installing the wellhead one of the rig hands was injured with a bar above his eyebrow."],["ALB0226SI002","06-Feb-26","Electrical Equipment Theft"]]}]},{"title":"STATUS","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"],["1","Conducted monthly safety meeting with Mechanics and technical support departments"],["2","Two SCBA drills done at L29 A and CTF."],["3","Safety induction and H2S training done for 9 employees."]]}]},{"title":"ACTIONS","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"],["1","Continue cooperating with tech support team for hot work permits 14 totals."],["2","15 Site Work Inspections, 1 Lease & 3 Safety inspection, 3 WAH equipment inspections done by HS Team"],["3","2 Tank trucks inspected and Truck master list updated."],["4","Four safety support by the HS team at M32A, N31C, and 2 at Fieri HUB"],["5","Two Gas readings and one driving test performed last week."],["6","86 fire extinguishers inspected and 7 fire suppression systems."],["7","Continued waste segregation and management at plastic site."],["8","Continued Ecopits level monitoring and management. Ecopit 7 actual level 5 cm. Ecopit receiving materials are; Ecopit 3 - level 16.5 cm and Ecopit 8 - level 12 cm. Continued moving water from Ecopit 8 to Ecopit 3 and from Ecopit 7 to Ecopit 6."],["9","Sent to NEA quarterly reporting of \"Oil and gas exploration and production\" permit."],["10","Sent to NEA yearly reporting and environmental management plan of 2026 for Ecopit 5."