  ('af9d7a08-96c0-5faf-bdec-80661132d2c6'::uuid, 'reservoir', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-02-23 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"23 Feb – 01 March 2026","starts_on":"2026-02-23","ends_on":"2026-03-01","department_id":"reservoir","paragraphs":["Based on the polymer pattern analysis, recommended to restart polymer injection of 5199, 5490 and 5805 for implementation.","Prepare the restart plan of SI producers, water injectors and polymer injectors to increase net oil production aiming at 1100m3/d in following months.","Three polymer producers have weekly production incremental higher than 1.5m3/d.","Recover from workover – 5057,5328,5458.","One polymer producers have weekly production loss equal/higher than 1.5 m3/d.","Well down – 5540","Unchanged the amount of active polymer injectors (17). There were some problems with the equipment when restarting the operations, mainly instrumentation","The only main facility in operation is the PSU300 at O34A (reached 90% capacity).","Daily injection volume 1330m3 (78.2 m3/d/well) or 40% of volume injection before SI period. Average daily polymer consumption is 1467 kg/d (1,95 bags/d). Store inventory 144 bags (on 1st March).","WHP are stabilized in almost all the injectors in operation","Daily monitoring of the status and inventory of our assets in the field continues.","Under strict monitor the 4 self-producing WSW in G1 and G2 zone due to high reservoir energy. Max casing pressure at WSW 963 at 200psi. Restarted WSW 3005 to monitor rate and pressure trend.","Leakage from the wellhead of 679 was found by our operator. It was fixed by service rig support team.","Communicated with the AMBU for their full bank details as per the request of our treasury department. The data will be sent by them via email.","Coordinate correction of 577 and 2173 has high cost. AMBU explained to us that the permit usage closure process must be done in e-Albania. The fee of this process was requested from the 3rd 