  ('eba07d27-6860-503f-9293-614b1a0e41ec'::uuid, 'geology', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-03-10 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"02-08 March 2026","starts_on":"2026-03-02","ends_on":"2026-03-08","department_id":"geology","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["PROJECT","PROJECT","CURRENT ACTIVITY/ISSUES"],["DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE"],["Active Drilling Update","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig"],["Reservoir Study and Development Well Optimization","Basic study for oil field development 1. The Geology Department held an internal meeting to discuss the work plan. Based on the current situation, the key priorities and responsibilities were assigned as follows: D1–M0 intervals: Update and correction of net pay thickness maps, and review of the well history of relevant vertical wells in areas belonging to Albpetro — Besnik and Geri. G3–G56 intervals: Update and correction of net pay thickness maps — William. Eastern fault zone: Sand body correlation and further refinement of geological understanding based on two newly drilled wells — Chenliang. Production-related analysis: Production analysis, water-injection well analysis, polymer-injection well analysis, and shut-in well reactivation analysis. The Geology team will maintain close communication with the Reservoir Department and provide necessary geological support. 2. Geri completed the preliminary justification materials for three new wells in the southern part of D3U. 3. Data and technical information were exchanged with the headquarters. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling","Basic study for oil field development 1. The Geology Department held an internal meeting to discuss the work plan. Based on the current situation, the key priorities and responsibilities were assigned as follows: D1–M0 intervals: Update and correction of net pay thickness maps, and review of the 