  ('eba07d27-6860-503f-9293-614b1a0e41ec'::uuid, 'reservoir', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-03-10 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"02-08 March 2026","starts_on":"2026-03-02","ends_on":"2026-03-08","department_id":"reservoir","paragraphs":["Finished the resuming plan of SI producers, water injectors and polymer injectors to increase net oil production aiming at 1100m3/d in following months","Analyze the performance changing pattern to figure out the reason and the way of improvement。","Monitor the performance of polymer flooding patterns.","Two polymer producers have weekly production incremental higher than 2m3/d.","Recovered from workover – 6099 and 5464.","Two polymer producers have weekly production loss equal/higher than 2 m3/d.","Work over – 6073","Pump efficiency drop—5027-L2","Unchanged the amount of active polymer injectors, just 17. On discussion the restart of other 5 injectors","The only main facility in operation is the PSU300 at O34A (reached 90% capacity). Necessary to restart another PSU when the no injector will be increased.","Daily injection volume 1330m3 (78.2 m3/d/well) or 40% of volume injection before SI period. Average daily polymer consumption is 1467 kg/d (1,95 bags/d). Store inventory 144 bags (on 1st March).","WHP are stabilized in almost all the injectors in operation","Daily monitoring of the status and inventory of our assets in the field continues.","Under strict monitor the 4 self-producing WSW in G1 and G2 zone due to high reservoir energy. Max casing pressure at WSW 963 at 200psi.","Complete water analyses for the WSW 1317.","Communicated with the AMBU for their full bank details as per the request of our treasury department. They insist on making the payment as before, only with the treasury code, even though the last Monday, they agreed to give us the full bank account number where we can make the payment.","Revoke of permit of 577 and 2173. Waiting 3rd party response for the fee of this servic