  ('8ebf9b18-ac05-5e09-84a3-5f0c21a3913f'::uuid, 'geology', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-03-15 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"09-15 March 2026","starts_on":"2026-03-09","ends_on":"2026-03-15","department_id":"geology","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["PROJECT","PROJECT","CURRENT ACTIVITY/ISSUES"],["DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE"],["Active Drilling Update","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig"],["Reservoir Study and Development Well Optimization","Basic study for oil field development 1. Analysis of the potential connectivity between wells 5029, 5597, and 5598. Supported the reservoir team in related studies by providing cross sections and information on one abandoned well. Carried out stratigraphic correlation for 50 wells in this area, and supplemented and improved logging interpretation results and curve data for 9 wells. 2. Worked together with the reservoir team to analyze the possibility that injected water from well 5600-MP channelled through well 5381-ABD and reached the surface at well 964-M. 3. Started compiling and summarizing previous new well placement proposals, and listed the remaining drillable locations for both thermal recovery and cold production wells. 4. The translation of the Biographies and Old Books of 6 vertical wells in southern part, 2337-P, 109-P, Dr268-P, Dr267-P, 2806-P, 1025-P, 516-P; 519-P; 1428-P; 1207-P; G623-P; 520-P; 445-P; 1213-P; 1378-P; 444-P; 1361-P. 5.Preliminary analysis for re-activating some wells. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling","Basic study for oil field development 1. Analysis of the potential connectivity between wells 5029, 5597, and 5598. Supported the reservoir team in related studies by providing cross sections and information on one abandoned well. Carried out stratigraphic correlation for 50 wells in this area, and supplemented and improved logging interpre