  ('db775aef-5117-5e7e-bd65-2e917eb1e145'::uuid, 'geology', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-03-22 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"16-22 March 2026","starts_on":"2026-03-16","ends_on":"2026-03-22","department_id":"geology","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["PROJECT","PROJECT","CURRENT ACTIVITY/ISSUES"],["DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE"],["Active Drilling Update","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig"],["Reservoir Study and Development Well Optimization","Basic study for oil field development 1. Screened reactivation potential of vertical well in the 5295 well area. 2. Completed the evaluation of reactivation potential for well 5188. 3. Completed the translation, compilation, and summary of well history for 17 old wells in the southern area of oilfield. 4. Updated and Improved perforation data in Petrel project, including the matching relation between well names and UWI. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling","Basic study for oil field development 1. Screened reactivation potential of vertical well in the 5295 well area. 2. Completed the evaluation of reactivation potential for well 5188. 3. Completed the translation, compilation, and summary of well history for 17 old wells in the southern area of oilfield. 4. Updated and Improved perforation data in Petrel project, including the matching relation between well names and UWI. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling","Basic study for oil field development 1. Screened reactivation potential of vertical well in the 5295 well area. 2. Completed the evaluation of reactivation potential for well 5188. 3. Completed the translation, compilation, and summary of well history for 17 old wells in the southern area of oilfield. 4. Updated and Improved perforation data in Petrel project, including the matching relation between well names and UWI. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling"]]}],"subsections":[{"title":"GEOLOGY AND DEVELOPMENT","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["PROJECT","PROJECT","CURRENT ACTIVITY/ISSUES"],["DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE"],["Active Drilling Update","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig"],["Reservoir Study and Development Well Optimization","Basic study for oil field development 1. Screened reactivation potential of vertical well in the 5295 well area. 2. Completed the evaluation of reactivation potential for well 5188. 3. Completed the translation, compilation, and summary of well history for 17 old wells in the southern area of oilfield. 4. Updated and Improved perforation data in Petrel project, including the matching relation between well names and UWI. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling","Basic study for oil field development 1. Screened reactivation potential of vertical well in the 5295 well area. 2. Completed the evaluation of reactivation potential for well 5188. 3. Completed the translation, compilation, and summary of well history for 17 old wells in the southern area of oilfield. 4. Updated and Improved perforation data in Petrel project, including the matching relation between well names and UWI. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling","Basic study for oil field development 1. Screened reactivation potential of vertical well in the 5295 well area. 2. Completed the evaluation of reactivation potential for well 5188. 3. Completed the translation, compilation, and summary of well history for 17 old wells in the southern area of oilfield. 4. Updated and Improved perforation data in Petrel project, including the matching relation between well names and UWI. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling"]]}]}]}'::jsonb, now()),
  ('db775aef-5117-5e7e-bd65-2e917eb1e145'::uuid, 'reservoir', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-03-22 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"16-22 March 2026","starts_on":"2026-03-16","ends_on":"2026-03-22","department_id":"reservoir","paragraphs":["Analyze the potential of the 5351-M0 well area, which was a 2013 waterflood pilot area and has been suspended production due to high water cut. Two wells in this area are preliminarily identified as having re-drill potential.","Held a meeting with the GEOLOGY Department and ENGINEERING & TECHNICAL Department to discuss 26 wells with improvement potential. It was agreed to continue Speed-up and monitor performance for 7 of these wells; 13 wells require retesting water cut, or further FDT data before considering speed-up.","Reviewd the initial draft of the PM Oilfield reserves report as for the end of 2025. An email has been sent to GCA requesting review and clarification regarding discrepancies in PDP reserves.","Actual Production Vs. 2026 Budget as of March 22nd , 2026","Two polymer producers have weekly production incremental higher than 2m3/d.","Water cut drop down after test – 5485.","Recovering after workover –6073.","Four polymer producers have weekly production loss equal/higher than 2 m3/d.","Work over – 5185","Waiting for Rig –6110 5368 5752.","Unchanged the amount of active polymer injectors, just 17. The restarts of other 5 injectors, as per the request of RET, will be done today, March 24.","The only main facility in operation is the PSU300 at O34A (reached 93% capacity). Also the PSU600 will restart today to supply the 2nd batch of polymer injectors. Will be operated with 2 zones.","Daily injection volume 1370m3 (78.2 m3/d/well) or 40% of volume injection before SI period. With the restart of 2nd group of injectors the volume injection will reach 1780m3/d.","Av. daily polymer consumption is 1465 kg/d (1,95 bags/d). Store inventory 106 bags (on 22 March). Estimated to reach 1816kg/d (2.42 bgs/d).","2 changes of volume targets were done in the last week to: 6108/M (+20m3/d) and 6189/D3U (+20m3/d)","Shut in the well 6189/D3U on 19 March due to increased transportation cost (no fresh water at M37A)","Daily monitoring of the status and inventory of our assets in the field continues.","Under strict monitor the 4 self-producing WSW in G1 and G2 zone due to high reservoir energy. Max casing pressure at WSW 963 at 200psi.","No any news from the director of ZABU (AMBU) Fier regarding the full bank account of their agency. Still waiting.","Revoke of permit of 577 and 2173. Ongoing the process.","Hot water with Surfactant and Viscosity Reducer, Huff & Puff.","Prepared and injected 500m3 0.2% VR6 solution to 6186/G5","5577/G4: to recover 1168m3; FDT 255m; Net 2.4m3/d","5284/G4: to recover 1751m3; FDT 101m; Net 2.5m3/d","5836/D3L: to recover 706m3; FDT 236m; Net 3.2m3/d","5614/G6: to recover 13819m3; on soaking time"],"tables":[{"rows":[["","Ave this week ( March 22nd, m3/d)","Ave this week ( March 22nd, m3/d)","Ave this week ( March 22nd, m3/d)","Cum production in YTD,m3","Cum production in YTD,m3","Cum production in YTD,m3"],["","Budget","Actual","Actual -Budget","Budget","Actual","Actual - Budget"],["Existing well","","941","-","","68,754","-"],["New non-thermal well","","0","-","","0","-"],["Polymer conversion","","0","-","","0","-"],["Reactivation+Stimulation","","0","-","","0","-"],["Thermal","","121","-","","9,798","-"],["Total","","1,062","-","","78,552","-"]]},{"rows":[["","","Oil Production m3/d","Oil Production m3/d","Variance"],["","","Last Week","This Week","+/- (m3/d)"],["Central","PF&WF","256.9","256.8","-0.1"],["North","PF","57.4","54.1","-3.3"],["South","PF","103.6","102.3","-1.3"],["EOR TOTAL","PF&WF","417.9","413.2","-4.8"]]},{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]},{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]},{"rows":[["Wells for Conversion","Injection well","PAD","Mixing Area","First Injection Date","Comments"],["1","5891/D3U","O32B","S","Februar