  ('5b9cfd11-1281-5807-9d2c-821cce68a8e3'::uuid, 'geology', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-03-29 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"23-29 March 2026","starts_on":"2026-03-23","ends_on":"2026-03-29","department_id":"geology","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["PROJECT","PROJECT","CURRENT ACTIVITY/ISSUES"],["DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE"],["Active Drilling Update","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig"],["Reservoir Study and Development Well Optimization","Basic study for oil field development 1. Completed a brief reactivation evaluation presentation for well 5759-D5. 2. Screened the reactivation potential of directional wells adjacent to 5172-D3U. Well 914-M shows potential for future liquid rate enhancement, while well 860-M has potential for additional perforation in the D layer. 3. Built geological models for the 5029-D3Land 5597-D5 and5598-D4 well area. The results suggest possible vertical connection between 5029-5597, which requires further validation using dynamic data. 4. Updated the Petrel project by incorporating log interpretation results for three wells and well top data for one well. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling","Basic study for oil field development 1. Completed a brief reactivation evaluation presentation for well 5759-D5. 2. Screened the reactivation potential of directional wells adjacent to 5172-D3U. Well 914-M shows potential for future liquid rate enhancement, while well 860-M has potential for additional perforation in the D layer. 3. Built geological models for the 5029-D3Land 5597-D5 and5598-D4 well area. The results suggest possible vertical connection between 5029-5597, which requires further validation using dynamic data. 4. Updated the Petrel project by incorporating log interpretation results for three wells and well top data for one well. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling","Basic study for oil field development 1. Completed a brief reactivation evaluation presentation for well 5759-D5. 2. Screened the reactivation potential of directional wells adjacent to 5172-D3U. Well 914-M shows potential for future liquid rate enhancement, while well 860-M has potential for additional perforation in the D layer. 3. Built geological models for the 5029-D3Land 5597-D5 and5598-D4 well area. The results suggest possible vertical connection between 5029-5597, which requires further validation using dynamic data. 4. Updated the Petrel project by incorporating log interpretation results for three wells and well top data for one well. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling"]]}],"subsections":[{"title":"GEOLOGY AND DEVELOPMENT","paragraphs":[],"tables":[{"rows":[["PROJECT","PROJECT","CURRENT ACTIVITY/ISSUES"],["DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE","DEVELOPMENT DRILLING UPDATE"],["Active Drilling Update","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig","Drilling Rig"],["Reservoir Study and Development Well Optimization","Basic study for oil field development 1. Completed a brief reactivation evaluation presentation for well 5759-D5. 2. Screened the reactivation potential of directional wells adjacent to 5172-D3U. Well 914-M shows potential for future liquid rate enhancement, while well 860-M has potential for additional perforation in the D layer. 3. Built geological models for the 5029-D3Land 5597-D5 and5598-D4 well area. The results suggest possible vertical connection between 5029-5597, which requires further validation using dynamic data. 4. Updated the Petrel project by incorporating log interpretation results for three wells and well top data for one well. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling","Basic study for oil field development 1. Completed a brief reactivation evaluation presentation for well 5759-D5. 2. Screened the reactivation potential of directional wells adjacent to 5172-D3U. Well 914-M shows potential for future liquid rate enhancement, while well 860-M has potential for additional perforation in the D layer. 3. Built geological models for the 5029-D3Land 5597-D5 and5598-D4 well area. The results suggest possible vertical connection between 5029-5597, which requires further validation using dynamic data. 4. Updated the Petrel project by incorporating log interpretation results for three wells and well top data for one well. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling","Basic study for oil field development 1. Completed a brief reactivation evaluation presentation for well 5759-D5. 2. Screened the reactivation potential of directional wells adjacent to 5172-D3U. Well 914-M shows potential for future liquid rate enhancement, while well 860-M has potential for additional perforation in the D layer. 3. Built geological models for the 5029-D3Land 5597-D5 and5598-D4 well area. The results suggest possible vertical connection between 5029-5597, which requires further validation using dynamic data. 4. Updated the Petrel project by incorporating log interpretation results for three wells and well top data for one well. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling"]]}]}]}'::jsonb, now()),
  ('5b9cfd11-1281-5807-9d2c-821cce68a8e3'::uuid, 'reservoir', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-03-29 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"23-29 March 2026","starts_on":"2026-03-23","ends_on":"2026-03-29","department_id":"reservoir","paragraphs":["Updated the work plan and production forecast of 2026 according to the actual situation.","Evaluated the potential of polymer patterns in SI, suggested to resume injection on 7 injectors.","Reviewed the initial draft of the PM Oilfield reserves report as of the end of 2025. The conclusion of report meets our expectation.","Actual Production Vs. 2026 Budget as of March 29th , 2026","Two polymer producers have weekly production incremental higher than 2m3/d.","Recovering after workover –5185 and 5995.","Two polymer producers have weekly production loss equal/higher than 2 m3/d.","Work over – 5368","Waiting for Rig –5435-L3.","The no of active polymer injectors increased to 27. The restart of 5 injectors was done on March 24. Another list with injectors to restart was sent by RET on March 25. These injectors were restarted on March 26 and 27.","Started operating the PSU600 on March 24. It is running with 32% capacity. Reduced the load to PSU 300 from 93% to 74%.","After completing the missing parts and equipment (used in other pads), injection unit of O31A was put back into operation to inject to 5478. Used B condition parts.","Daily injection volume 2050m3 (78.84 m3/d/well) or 650% of volume injection before SI period. The injection at 6189/D3U continues stopped (transportation cost and monitoring patterns)","Av. daily polymer consumption in the last 3 days is 2000 kg/d (2.67bags/d). Stops by power affected the daily consumption.","Store inventory 100 bags (on 29 March). We are waiting for the FP3630S delivery in the field.","Increment of WHP observed at 6108/M (pad L31A). Negative affected also by the consecutive and prolonged injection interruption caused by power issues.","Under strict monitor the 4 self-producing WSW in G1 and G2 zone due to high reservoir energy. Max casing pressure at WSW 963 at 200psi.","7 WSW are in production. Fresh water quality remains good in all of them.","Hot water with Surfactant and Viscosity Reducer, Huff & Puff.","Ongoing maintenance works by tech support and mechanics to 60m3 mixer in the preparation unit","5577/G4: to recover 1157m3; FDT 255m; Net 2.4m3/d","5284/G4: to recover 1733m3; FDT 101m; Net 2.5m3/d","5836/D3L: to recover 616m3; FDT 217m; Net 3.2m3/d","5614/G6: to recover 13819m3; on soaking time"],"tables":[{"rows":[["","Ave this week ( March 29th, m3/d)","Ave this week ( March 29th, m3/d)","Ave this week ( March 29th, m3/d)","Cum production in YTD,m3","Cum production in YTD,m3","Cum production in YTD,m3"],["","Budget","Actual","Actual -Budget","Budget","Actual","Actual - Budget"],["Existing well","","887","-","","74,946","-"],["New non-thermal well","","0","-","","0","-"],["Polymer conversion","","0","-","","0","-"],["Reactivation+Stimulation","","0","-","","0","-"],["Thermal","","103","-","","10,532","-"],["Total","","989","-","","85,478","-"]]},{"rows":[["","","Oil Production m3/d","Oil Production m3/d","Variance"],["","","Last Week","This Week","+/- (m3/d)"],["Central","PF&WF","256.5","219.7","-36.8"],["North","PF","54.1","45.0","-9.1"],["South","PF","102.1","82.8","-19.3"],["EOR TOTAL","PF&WF","412.7","347.5","-65.2"]]},{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]},{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]},{"rows":[["Wells for Conversion","Injection well","PAD","Mixing Area","First Injection Date","Comments"]]},{"rows":[["Single Rig SS18 and SS19","4 jobs completed by Single Rig SS18 and SS19"],["Flush by Rig SS17","11 jobs completed by Flush by rig SS17"],["Rig less Jobs","1 wells/jobs - completed by Rig less"]]},{"rows":[["Type","Comment"],["Injector wells","None"]]},{"rows":[["Type","Comment"],["Reactivation wells","None"]]},{"rows":[["Type","Comment"],["New drilled wells","None"]]},{"rows":[["Type","Comment"],["WIII