 New drilling Geological design Material for drilling","Basic study for oil field development 1.Gas Production and Geological Analysis Completed two presentations of gas production performance and geological characteristics of the G3, D, M0M, M1, and M2 layers to support gas potential evaluation. 2. Data Compilation and Analysis Compiled and organized sand data and single-well section for M-0M in wells 5005, 5006, and 5007 to support gas potential evaluation. 3. Geological Modeling – 5575-G3 well Area Completed geological model in 5575-G3 area and conducted a preliminary assessment of gas potential in the G3 reservoir. 4. Geological Modeling – 5992-M2 Well Area Completed geological model for 5992-M2 area and analyzed distribution of lateral section within M1 and M2 layers to provide a basis for reactivating the offset deviation wells. 5. Petrel Data Management and Interpretation Update Updated *.lic files for three wells in the Petrel project. Improved well log interpretation results for eight wells. New drilling Geological design Material for drilling"]]}]}]}'::jsonb, now()),
  ('2393b7f4-ec9b-5925-9030-38b81ffdd313'::uuid, 'reservoir', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-04-05 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"30 March – 05 April 2026","starts_on":"2026-03-30","ends_on":"2026-04-05","department_id":"reservoir","paragraphs":["Analyzed the potential to increase natural gas production.","Evaluated the potential of vertical wells’ reactivation on or near the existing PAD which could get support from injectors.","Completed the summary of development technologies implemented in Kucova oilfield, which will be presented to Albpetrol and AKBN.","Actual Production Vs. 2026 Budget as of April 5th , 2026","Three polymer producers have weekly production incremental higher than 2m3/d.","Recovering after workover –5368.","Getting support from injectors—6146 and 5924","Two polymer producers have weekly production loss equal/higher than 2 m3/d.","Work over – 5435-L3","FDT drop down –5650.","The average injection volume in the last week was 2073m3/d from 1730m3/d or 343m3/d more than the previous week. The main issues have been:","Stop injection on 5 April due to electrical works in South area. PSU300 was affected","Operational issues (electrical and instrumental)","Restarted polymer injector 5802/M on 2 April. Changed viscosity target at P28A injectors from 50cPs to 30cPs.","The injector 6189/D3U remains shut in","Normal operation to PSU300 (run with 73%) and PSU600 (run with 35%).","Av. daily polymer consumption in the last week is 2.86bags/d. Stock in store are 72 bags (on 5 April). We are waiting FP3630S delivery in the field the next days.","The main changed has been: Increment of WHP to 5904/M0U (start reducing injection rate on it), the increment of WHP to 5801/M0M and 5805/D5 and fluctuation of WHP to 6108/M (affected by the stops)","Under strict monitor the 4 self-producing WSW in G1 and G2 zone due to high reservoir energy. Max casing pressure at WSW 963/G1 at 180psi. Plan to restart WSW 3005/G1 if required","7 WSW are in production. 760/M is producing exclusively for the boiler to N29E. Fresh water quality remains good in all of them.","Confirmation of payment of invoices (water consumption in Q4-2025) for AMBU was received from our finance department.","Hot water with Surfactant and Viscosity Reducer, Huff & Puff.","Were completed the maintenance works by tech support and mechanics to 60m3 mixer in the preparation unit. Have been prepared 20m3 5% VR6 solution in it.","5577/G4: to recover 1138m3; FDT 255m; Net 2.2m3/d","5284/G4: to recover 1733m3;","5836/D3L: to recover 512m3; FDT 228m; Net 3.2m3/d","5614/G6: to recover 13819m3; on soaking time"],"tables":[{"rows":[["","Ave this week ( April 5th, m3/d)","Ave this week ( April 5th, m3/d)","Ave this week ( April 5th, m3/d)","Cum production in YTD,m3","Cum production in YTD,m3","Cum production in YTD,m3"],["","Budget","Actual","Actual -Budget","Budget","Actual","Actual - Budget"],["Existing well","","915","-","","81,283","-"],["New non-thermal well","","0","-","","0","-"],["Polymer conversion","","0","-","","0","-"],["Reactivation+Stimulation","","0","-","","0","-"],["Thermal","","109","-","","11,363","-"],["Total","","1,024","-","","92,646","-"]]},{"rows":[["","","Oil Production m3/d","Oil Production m3/d","Variance"],["","","Last Week","This Week","+/- (m3/d)"],["Central","PF&WF","245.8","247.3","1.5"],["North","PF","50.4","52.5","2.1"],["South","PF","91.9","92.5","0.6"],["EOR TOTAL","PF&WF","388.1","392.3","4.2"]]},{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]},{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]},{"rows":[["Wells for Conversion","Injection well","PAD","Mixing Area","First Injection Date","Comments"]]},{"rows":[["Single Rig SS18 and SS19","4 jobs completed by Single Rig SS18 and SS19"],["Flush by Rig SS17","11 jobs completed by Flush by rig SS17"],["Rig less Jobs","2 wells/jobs - completed by Rig less"]]},{"rows":[["Type","Comment"],["Injector wells","None"]]},{"rows":[["Type","Comment"],["Reactivation wells","None"]]},{"rows":[["Ty