,"388.1","392.3","4.2"]]}]},{"title":"EOR","paragraphs":[],"tables":[]},{"title":"6.2.1 POLYMER","paragraphs":["The average injection volume in the last week was 2073m3/d from 1730m3/d or 343m3/d more than the previous week. The main issues have been:","Stop injection on 5 April due to electrical works in South area. PSU300 was affected","Operational issues (electrical and instrumental)","Restarted polymer injector 5802/M on 2 April. Changed viscosity target at P28A injectors from 50cPs to 30cPs.","The injector 6189/D3U remains shut in","Normal operation to PSU300 (run with 73%) and PSU600 (run with 35%).","Av. daily polymer consumption in the last week is 2.86bags/d. Stock in store are 72 bags (on 5 April). We are waiting FP3630S delivery in the field the next days.","The main changed has been: Increment of WHP to 5904/M0U (start reducing injection rate on it), the increment of WHP to 5801/M0M and 5805/D5 and fluctuation of WHP to 6108/M (affected by the stops)"],"tables":[{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]}]},{"title":"6.2.2 OTHERS","paragraphs":["Under strict monitor the 4 self-producing WSW in G1 and G2 zone due to high reservoir energy. Max casing pressure at WSW 963/G1 at 180psi. Plan to restart WSW 3005/G1 if required","7 WSW are in production. 760/M is producing exclusively for the boiler to N29E. Fresh water quality remains good in all of them.","Confirmation of payment of invoices (water consumption in Q4-2025) for AMBU was received from our finance department.","Hot water with Surfactant and Viscosity Reducer, Huff & Puff.","Were completed the maintenance works by tech support and mechanics to 60m3 mixer in the preparation unit. Have been prepared 20m3 5% VR6 solution in it.","5577/G4: to recover 1138m3; FDT 255m; Net 2.2m3/d","5284/G4: to recover 1733m3;","5836/D3L: to recover 512m3; FDT 228m; Net 3.2m3/d","5614/G6: to recover 13819m3; on soaking time"],"tables":[{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]}]},{"title":"6.2.3 NEW CONVERSION 2026","paragraphs":