  ('533b9bc4-5caf-5732-b6e8-dec1b85b89d0'::uuid, 'reservoir', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-04-12 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"06-12 April 2026","starts_on":"2026-04-06","ends_on":"2026-04-12","department_id":"reservoir","paragraphs":["Monitor the production performance of all wells; analyze the wells with change of production.","Evaluated the potential of vertical wells’ reactivation on or near the existing PAD which could get support from injectors. Three of them have potential for reactivation.","Sent the predicted oil prices to the GCA for sensitivity analysis according to the request of headquarter. We are still awaiting the final feedback from headquarters about the reserve assessment.","Checked and sent out the 4th batch of polymer injectors for resumption when the 120 bags of powder arrived.","Actual Production Vs. 2026 Budget as of April 12th , 2026","Two polymer producers have weekly production incremental higher than 2m3/d.","Recovered after workover –5368 and 6110.","Five polymer producers have weekly production loss equal/higher than 2 m3/d.","Work over – 5426-L3, 5356 and 5808","Water cut increase –6100 and 6146.","The average injection volume in the last week was 2217m3/d from 2073m3/d or 144m3/d more than the previous week. The main issues have been:","Stop of PSU600 on 9 and 10 April due to instrument malfunction","Operational issues (electrical and mechanics problems). Also a lot of modifications or adjustments to restart the new list of wells were done.","Restarted injection in 9 other wells. Active injectors are 35.","It was stopped injection to 5421/D3U to monitor producers wells","The injector 6189/D3U remains SI. Transportation cost and producers performance","Normal operation to PSU300 (run with 80%). PSU600 is running with 41%.","Av. daily polymer consumption reached 3.3 bags. Stocks in store are only 45 bags (on 14 April). We are waiting FP3630S delivery in the field.","The main changes have been: Drop of injection rate by 14m3/d to 5191/D2 (increased WHP), by 10m3/d to 5904/M0U (increased WHP) and by 12m3d to 5101/D3-L2 (increased WHP). Also, stabilized the WHP to 5801/M0M and 5805/D5.","Under strict monitor the 4 self-producing WSW in G1 and G2 zone due to high reservoir energy. Max casing pressure at WSW 963/G1 at 160psi. Plan to restart WSW 1467/G1","9 WSW are in production. 760/M is producing exclusively for the boiler to N29E. Fresh water quality remains good in all of them.","Hot water with Surfactant and Viscosity Reducer, Huff & Puff.","6002/M - Were completed the preparation for the next VR6 stimulation. The program is to inject 1000m3 0.2% VR6.","5577/G4: to recover 1125m3; FDT 255m; Net 2.2m3/d","5284/G4: to recover 1733m3; FDT 1176m","5836/D3L: to recover 437m3; FDT 228m; Net 3.2m3/d","5614/G6: to recover 13819m3; on soaking time"],"tables":[{"rows":[["","Ave this week ( April 12th, m3/d)","Ave this week ( April 12th, m3/d)","Ave this week ( April 12th, m3/d)","Cum production in YTD,m3","Cum production in YTD,m3","Cum production in YTD,m3"],["","Budget","Actual","Actual -Budget","Budget","Actual","Actual - Budget"],["Existing well","","888","-","","87,498","-"],["New non-thermal well","","0","-","","0","-"],["Polymer conversion","","0","-","","0","-"],["Reactivation+Stimulation","","0","-","","0","-"],["Thermal","","101","-","","12,069","-"],["Total","","989","-","","99,566","-"]]},{"rows":[["","","Oil Production m3/d","Oil Production m3/d","Variance"],["","","Last Week","This Week","+/- (m3/d)"],["Central","PF&WF","247.3","237.1","-10.2"],["North","PF","52.5","52.3","-0.2"],["South","PF","92.5","88.0","-4.5"],["EOR TOTAL","PF&WF","392.4","377.4","-15.0"]]},{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]},{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]},{"rows":[["Wells for Conversion","Injection well","PAD","Mixing Area","First Injection Date","Comments"]]},{"rows":[["Single Rig SS18 and SS19","6 jobs completed by Single Rig SS18 and SS19"],["Flush by Rig SS17","9 jobs