  ('96981f57-7e05-52b2-9b18-9f8271f4d0f3'::uuid, 'reservoir', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-04-19 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"13-19 April 2026","starts_on":"2026-04-13","ends_on":"2026-04-19","department_id":"reservoir","paragraphs":["Completed the development summary for the meeting with AKBN.","Sent the sensitivity analysis to headquarter according to the predicted oil prices. The reserve assessment got approval.","Analyzed the change of water cut of 5927-D3U, suggest to isolate 819-P。","Start to set the candidates of isolation based on the obligation disposal plan.","Actual Production Vs. 2026 Budget as of April 19th , 2026","Two polymer producers have weekly production incremental higher than 2m3/d.","Recovered after workover –6110.","Recovering after workover –5435.","Tree polymer producers have weekly production loss equal/higher than 2 m3/d.","Work over – 5426-L3 and 5261;","Water cut increase –5927-D3U.","The average injection volume in the last week was 2452m3/d from 2217m3/d or 235m3/d more than the previous week. The main issues have been:","5 hrs stop of PSU600 on 14 April due to electric grid problem. Affected C+N areas","Operational issues (mechanic and instrument problems). Problems in power end of J165 pump at N28A were found. It will be moved to pad D for further investigation. Also, under investigation the causes of PSU cone overflow at PSU600.","Active injectors are 35. In the last week all of them were injecting to 100% of target rate. While two from reactivated ones remains SI for monitoring","Normal operation to PSU300 (run with 80%). PSU600 is running with 40%.","Av. daily polymer consumption reached 3.4 bags. Stocks in store are 131 bags (on 19 April). The delivery of 120 bgs FP3630S in the field was completed on 17 April.","The main changes in injector’s performance during the last week have been: Drop of injection rate by 14m3/d to 5191/D2, by 17m3/d to 5904/M0U and by 7m3d to 5101/D3-L2.","WHP of 6