  ('b21095b0-3259-5e40-8555-165c82d09ab1'::uuid, 'reservoir', 'approved'::entry_status, '{"source_file":"2026-04-26 Weekly Information Report (1).docx","report_label":"20-26 April 2026","starts_on":"2026-04-20","ends_on":"2026-04-26","department_id":"reservoir","paragraphs":["Confirm 23 candidates of isolation based on the obligation disposal plan.","Analyze the current productivity. There are 27 producers needing rig and 15 producers having potential of reactivation.","Analyze the water intrusion issue in some areas. Will put the risk wells into the well list of isolation.","Actual Production Vs. 2026 Budget as of April 26th , 2026","Three polymer producers have weekly production incremental higher than 2m3/d.","Recovered after workover –5534, 5328 and 5578.","Tree polymer producers have weekly production loss equal/higher than 2 m3/d.","Need rig – 5026 and 5905","The average injection volume in the last week was 2382m3/d from 2452m3/d or 70m3/d less than the previous week. The main issues have been:","From 1 to 3.5 hrs stop due to works in Jagodina power substation on 20 April. Affected S+SW and P27B, P28A, N25B in C+N","Operational issues (instrument problem in PSU 600). Were found the causes of PSU cone overflow at PSU600. Obligated to change the line design as it was not possible to modify the parameters (we are waiting for reprograming of the PLC).","Active injectors are 33. It was SI 5904/M0U as per the request of RET and 5393/D4 due to facility limitation. While two from reactivated ones remains SI for monitoring","Normal operation to PSU300 (run with 80%). PSU600 is running with 38%.","Av. daily polymer consumption was 3.4 bags. Stocks in store are 251 bags (on 26 April). The 2nd batch of polymer powder was delivered in the last week.","The main changes in injector’s performance during the last week have been: Drop of injection rate by 7m3/d to 5191/D2, by 6m3d to 5101/D3-L2, but the most sensitive was the drop of injection rate to 5801/M0M by 36m3/d (almost 50%)","WHP of 6108/M increased to 1700psi after the stop on 20 April but it drop slowly to 1450psi until 26 April","Under strict monitor the 4 self-producing WSW in G1 and G2 zone due to high reservoir energy. Max casing pressure at WSW 963/G1 remains at 160psi.","9 WSW are in production. Fresh water quality remains good in all of them. Supplied normally the boiler","The fresh water consumptions based on water sources flowmeter reading for Q1-2026 were obtained by AMBU (ZABU Fier) specialists.","Hot water with Surfactant and Viscosity Reducer, Huff & Puff.","6002/M – Started production; FDT 508m; W/C 100%","5577/G4: to recover 1096m3; FDT 255m; Net 2.2m3/d","5284/G4: to recover 1733m3; FDT 1176m","5836/D3L: to recover 251m3; FDT 227m; Net 3.4m3/d","5614/G6: to recover 13819m3; on soaking time"],"tables":[{"rows":[["","Ave this week ( April 26th, m3/d)","Ave this week ( April 26th, m3/d)","Ave this week ( April 26th, m3/d)","Cum production in YTD,m3","Cum production in YTD,m3","Cum production in YTD,m3"],["","Budget","Actual","Actual -Budget","Budget","Actual","Actual - Budget"],["Existing well","928","876","-52","102,220","99,751","-2469"],["New non-thermal well","0","0","0","0","0","0"],["Polymer conversion","0","0","0","0","0","0"],["Reactivation+Stimulation","0","0","0","0","0","0"],["Thermal","124","87","-37","14,584","13,386","-1198"],["Total","1,052","963","-89","116,804","113,137","-3667"]]},{"rows":[["","","Oil Production m3/d","Oil Production m3/d","Variance"],["","","Last Week","This Week","+/- (m3/d)"],["Central","PF&WF","230.3","238.8","8.4"],["North","PF","50.9","48.2","-2.7"],["South","PF","88.6","89.2","0.6"],["EOR TOTAL","PF&WF","369.9","376.2","6.3"]]},{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]},{"rows":[["ID","Brief Description"]]},{"rows":[["Wells for Conversion","Injection well","PAD","Mixing Area","First Injection Date","Comments"]]},{"rows":[["Double rig and Single Rigs SS18/SS19","7 jobs completed by Double rig and Single Rigs SS18/SS19"],["Flush 